            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "The features required in the application were analyzed in the requirements part of the development model, where we analyzed all the different features this project could incorporate in order to prove useful. In this model of software development the requirements are first analyzed and separated into different increments. After all the features were identified, they were classified into various increments. In this project,we had planned 5 initial increments for the development process to be divided into,the increments are defined as; user interface, OCR for text elements, OCR for non-text elements, file compression and file format conversion.",
            "block_bbox": [
                212,
                167,
                1046,
                483
            ],
            "block_id": 0,
            "block_order": 1
        },
        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "Each increment was completed iteratively where each iteration has its own planning,design, implementation and testing. Then the plan for each iteration was made developed, implemented and tested until all the iterations of the increment were finished. Each increment expanded on the features of the prior increment which led to having a prototype ready for use before the completion of the project.",
            "block_bbox": [
                211,
                523,
                1045,
                714
            ],
            "block_id": 1,
            "block_order": 2
        },
        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "Thus, after the development of a few increments finished they were integrated into a single application. This model allowed us to work on each individual increment on our own and integrate them all at the end. The increments we decided on working first were- the user interface, file compression, file conversion and ocr processing.",
